President Obama spoke with King Salman bin Abdulaziz al-Saud of Saudi Arabia to discuss recent developments in Yemen. The President expressed the United States' support for Saudi Arabia's actions in response to President Hadi's request and in support of the legitimate government of Yemen. Both leaders emphasized the goal of achieving lasting stability in Yemen through a negotiated political solution facilitated by the United Nations and involving all parties as outlined in the GCC Initiative. The President also reaffirmed the strong friendship between the United States and Saudi Arabia and reiterated our commitment to Saudi Arabia's security.